##  TrackHover

track which element is being hovered

properties.name: trackHover
properties.description:
`trackHover` set true if selector listen to mouseenter/mouseleave events and set hoveredItem accordingly.
When true, this element also and fires `multi-mouseenter` and multi-mouseleave.

properties.name: hovered
properties.description:
`hovered` the hovered item, tracked when `trackHover` is set to true.
This is usefull for instance when we want to highlight the legend being hovered

methods.name: attachListeners
methods.description:
`attachListeners` listen to click, mouseenter and mouseleave and
fires their respective `multi` events (`multi-tap`, `multi-mouse-enter` and `multi-mouse-leave`)

methods.name: _observerHovered
methods.description: `_observerHoveredItem` add `.hovered` class to all items with same key as hovered

## MultiChartContainerAxis

`<multi-container-axis>` a container for coordinate data

properties.name: enableZoom
properties.description: `enableZoom` set true to enable zoom behaviors

properties.name: extent
properties.description: [`extent`] (https://github.com/d3/d3-zoom#zoom_extent) sets the viewport extent to the specified array of points [[x0, y0], [x1, y1]]

properties.name: scaleExtent
properties.description: [`scaleExtent`](https://github.com/d3/d3-zoom#zoom_scaleExtent) sets the scale extent to the specified array of numbers [k0, k1] where k0 is the minimum allowed scale factor and k1 is the maximum allowed scale factor, and returns this zoom behavior.

properties.name: data
properties.description: `data` to display the chart

properties.name: margin
properties.description:
`margin` applied to svg container (not css margin, wich can also be applied as per normal css rules)
By default margins are slightly bigger than for simple `multi-container-svg`

properties.name: scales
properties.description:
`scales` key-value [scale](https://github.com/d3/d3-scale) for the active axis. `bottom` and `left` scales are always calculated. `right` and `top` scales are set only when
right and top axis is drawn.

properties.name: domains
properties.description: `domains` key-value [domain](https://github.com/d3/d3-scale#domain) for active axis. By default, `{bottom: bottomDomain, left:leftDomain}`

properties.name: ranges
properties.description: `ranges` key-value [range](https://github.com/d3/d3-scale#range) for active axis.

properties.name: accessors
properties.description: `accessors` key-value accessor functions for active axis.

properties.name: topAxis
properties.description: `topAxis` true to display top axis

properties.name: rightAxis
properties.description: `rightAxis` true to display right axis

properties.name: bottomAxis
properties.description: `bottomAxis` true to display bottom axis

properties.name: leftAxis
properties.description: `leftAxis` true to display left axis

properties.name: serieValueDomain
properties.description:
`serieValueDomain` value domain for each serie groupName, calculated in `multi-register-mixin`
if no groupName is given a default `default` name is given. Hence this field results to serieValueDomain = {default: [min, max]}

properties.name: serieOrdinalDomain
properties.description: `serieOrdinalDomain` ordinal domain for series

properties.name: serieDomainMapping
properties.description:
`serieDomainMapping` a mapping object that will make sure that scale domains are properly set when we use data series.
the default mapping will use value domain for left axis and ordinal domain for bottom axis

properties.name: ordinalDomainMapper
properties.description: `ordinalDomainMapper` a mapper for serie ordinal valued.

methods.name: _onSetValueDomain
methods.description:
`_onSetValueDomain` some charts will reset domain according to reshaped values (e.g. stack chart)
This provides a way to listing to those changes.

## MultiChartLine

`<multi-chart-line>` an element for displaying data as a line chart.

### Example

```html
	<multi-chart-line
       id="chart"
       color-scale="[[colorScale]]"
       data="[[data]]"

        <multi-serie key="[[item.key]]" label="[[item.label]]" accessor="{{item.accessor}}"></multi-serie>
        <!-- we need a accessor for y-scale -->
        <multi-accessor accessor="{{item.accessor}}" path="+value.[[item.key]]"></multi-accessor>
       </template>
     </dom-repeat>
   </multi-chart-line>
```

`<multi-legend>` a element for displaying chart legends
Relying on [d3-legend](https://d3-legend.susielu.com/), A library to make legends in svg-land easy as pie.

### Styling
`<multi-drawable-feature>` provides the following custom properties and mixins
for styling:

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--multi-legend-color` | text color for legends | `#292929`
`--multi-legend-background` | background color for legenx box | `#efefef`
`--multi-legend-stroke` | stroke color for legend box | `none`
`--multi-legend-opacity` | opacity for legend box | `0.6`
`--multi-legend` | Mixin applied to legend | `{}`

or property. Hyphenated values are converted to camel case when used to
look up the property of a selectable element. Camel cased values are
*not* converted to hyphenated values for attribute lookup. It's
recommended that you provide the hyphenated form of the name so that
selection works in both cases. (Use `attr-or-property-name` instead of
`attrOrPropertyName`.)
